    "updated_at": "2014-11-22T17:22:14Z",
    "body": "Thinking about it, should there be a `filename_str` and `dirname_str` at\nall? Or would it be safer to just have `filename/dirname` and `filename_display/dirname_display`?\n\nBecause even if `filename_str` would return something in the case of invalid characters,\nthe returned filename wouldn't represent the real filename, so operating\nwith it might result into an error.\n",
